Pluralism and pragmatism in a secular state.
At a time when Swiss voters have asked for a ban on the construction of minarets and there is a widespread alert to the alleged Islamization of Europe, John Bowen, an American academic, has written a detailed and studied report on the possible integration of Muslims (which are actually integrating) into one of the continent’s most openly secular societies.
Some readers will come to this new book as fans of the author's latest work "Why the French don't like veils" (2006), an elegant and detailed study of a problem that divided and worried the country for a decade and a half, and whose effects are still perceived today.
